<heading id="3E1D4846FFE6FFD9FF71FC24FDDAFBBE" bold="true" box="[151,551,1014,1041]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="4">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FF71FC24FDDAFBBE" authority="(Schaus, 1911)" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[151,551,1014,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguina">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FF71FC24FDDAFBBE" bold="true" box="[151,551,1014,1041]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FF71FC24FE89FBBE" bold="true" box="[151,372,1014,1041]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Eudocima anguina</emphasis>
(Schaus, 1911)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFE6FFD9FF71FBC8FECBFA32" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FBC8FE83FB9B" blockId="14.[151,1436,1014,1437]" box="[151,382,1050,1077]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE6FFD9FF79FBC8FF14FB9B" box="[159,233,1050,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionText="FIGURE 7. Neotropical Eudocima and Ferenta adults (dorsal aspect)." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs 7</figureCitation>
: A–B, 23: H)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FBECFECBFA32" blockId="14.[151,1436,1014,1437]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE6FFD9FF71FBECFEB8FBF7" author="Schaus, W." box="[151,325,1086,1113]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="173 - 193" refId="ref40161" refString="Schaus, W. (1911 b) New species of Heterocera from Costa Rica - IV. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 8, 7 (38), 173 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931108692920" type="journal article" year="1911">Schaus (1911b)</bibRefCitation>
raised the possibility that this species was conspecific with 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FC04FBEDFB84FBF6" box="[994,1145,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FC04FBEDFB88FBF6" authorityName="Phalaena" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[994,1141,1086,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collusoria">E. collusoria</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but these two species differ in wing shape, pattern, and COI 5’ characters. This is one of the three smallest Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FB4FFBB0FA8CFBD2" box="[1193,1393,1122,1148]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FB4FFBB0FAE6FBD2" box="[1193,1307,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Eudocima</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="A21252CFFFE6FFD9FA99FBB0FF38FB0F" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="32.0">32 mm</quantity>
, n=2), along with 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FE77FB55FDD9FB0E" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[401,548,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorans">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FE77FB55FDD9FB0E" box="[401,548,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. memorans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="A21252CFFFE6FFD9FDD5FB54FD78FB0F" box="[563,645,1158,1185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="33.0">33 mm</quantity>
, n=1) and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FD1DFB55FC71FB0E" authorityName="Phalaena" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[763,908,1158,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collusoria">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FD1DFB55FC71FB0E" box="[763,908,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. collusoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="A21252CFFFE6FFD9FC7CFB54FBEBFB0F" box="[922,1046,1158,1185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="34.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="34.0">34–35 mm</quantity>
, n=2). Of the three only 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FACFFB55FA61FB0E" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1321,1436,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguina">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FACFFB55FA61FB0E" box="[1321,1436,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E anguina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a fairly straight rather than strongly concave apical line. The forewing of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FBE3FB79FB7CFB6A" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1029,1153,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguina">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FBE3FB79FB7CFB6A" box="[1029,1153,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. anguina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more pointed apex and tornal hook, and more angular outer margin relative to the other two species. Also, only 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FB41FB1DFADFFB46" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1191,1314,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguina">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FB41FB1DFADFFB46" box="[1191,1314,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. anguina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks dark hairs and scales in the dorsal hindwing basal area. The hindwing medial patch may be absent (
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE6FFD9FB2DFB20FADCFAA2" box="[1227,1313,1266,1292]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[220,1372,193,1950]" captionTargetId="figure-32@76.[207,1381,181,1956]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 23. Eudocima, Ferenta and Graphigona adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605572/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
: H). When present the patch does not extend anterior of vein Cu1, whereas in the other two species it extends to vein M2 or beyond. The female dorsal forewing has a white spot on the basal side of the PM line between veins Cu2 and Cu1, lacking in the other two species. This species is rarely recorded from Columbia (Vargas-Fonseca 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FB3FFA8DFAF6FAD6" box="[1241,1291,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2020) north to 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FF52FA50FECFFA32" box="[180,306,1410,1436]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
